Calypsonet Terminal Calypso API - 1.0.4
  • All Classes
 

All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary Enum Summary Exception Summary 
    Class Description
    AtomicTransactionException
    Indicates that the transaction cannot be done in an atomic way because the capacity of the session buffer is not sufficient.
    AuthenticationNotVerifiedException
    Indicates that the card has correctly closed the secure session, but that it is impossible to check the authenticity of the support because the SAM is no more available (timeout, network problem,...).
    CalypsoApiProperties
    API properties.
    CalypsoCard
    A dynamic view of the card's content, regularly updated from the selection stage to the end of the transaction.
    CalypsoCard.ProductType
    All Calypso Card products supported by this API.
    CalypsoCardSelection
    Card specific CardSelection providing means to filter cards, select applications and define optional commands to be executed during the selection phase.
    CalypsoCardSelection.FileControlInformation
    Types of templates available in return for the Select Application command, according to the ISO7816-4 standard.
    CalypsoCardSelection.FileOccurrence
    Navigation options through the different applications contained in the card according to the ISO7816-4 standard.
    CalypsoSam
    A static and partial view of the SAM's content.
    CalypsoSam.ProductType
    All Calypso SAM products supported by this API.
    CalypsoSamSelection
    SAM specific CardSelection providing means to filter SAM and define optional commands to be executed during the selection phase such as the Unlock command.
    CardAnomalyException
    Indicates an anomaly in the card.
    CardCloseSecureSessionException
    Indicates that the card has refused the secure session closing.
    CardIOException
    Indicates a communication error with the card.
    CardRevokedException
    Indicates that the card is revoked.
    CardSecuritySetting
    Data to manage the security operations of a Calypso transaction.
    CardTransactionException
    Parent abstract class of all Calypso card transaction functional exceptions.
    CardTransactionManager
    Service providing the high-level API to manage transactions with a Calypso card.
    DesynchronizedExchangesException
    Indicates a desynchronization of the APDU exchanges.
    DirectoryHeader
    Calypso DF metadata.
    ElementaryFile
    Calypso Elementary File.
    ElementaryFile.Type
    The different types of EF.
    FileData
    Calypso EF content.
    FileHeader
    Calypso EF metadata.
    GetDataTag
    Enumeration of all supported tags for the Get Data command.
    InconsistencyDataException
    Indicates an inconsistency in the card data.
    SamAnomalyException
    Indicates an anomaly in the SAM.
    SamIOException
    Indicates a communication error with the SAM (e.g timeout, network,...).
    SamRevokedException
    Indicates that the SAM is revoked.
    SelectFileControl
    Enumeration of all expected behaviors of the selection command (see the specifics of this command in the ISO7816-4 standard and the Calypso specification).
    SessionAuthenticationException
    Indicates that the card has correctly closed the secure session, but the support is not authentic because the signature of the card is incorrect.
    SvAction
    Defines the type Stored Value of action.
    SvAuthenticationException
    Indicates that the "Stored Value" session is not authentic because the signature of the card is incorrect.
    SvDebitLogRecord
    Record of a Stored Value debit log.
    SvLoadLogRecord
    Record of a Stored Value load log.
    SvOperation
    Defines the type of Stored Value operation to be performed.
    UnauthorizedKeyException
    Indicates that the current card requires an unauthorized key.
    WriteAccessLevel
    Enumeration of the write access levels for the Calypso card Secure Session.
